6:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-12","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Rate Mechanics"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Both exchanges calculate funding rates using the same 8-hour interval and premium/discount methodology. Binance's deeper liquidity often results in more stable funding rates, particularly on major pairs like BTC and ETH. OKX funding rates can be more volatile on lower-cap altcoins due to thinner order books. Both platforms use similar interest rate components (typically 0.01% per 8 hours) but Binance's larger trader base creates more consistent rate convergence. Portfolio margin on OKX can affect effective funding costs through cross-collateralization benefits."}]]}]
7:["$","$Lb",null,{"items":[{"question":"Which exchange has lower funding rates for BTC perpetuals?","answer":"Binance typically maintains more stable funding rates due to deeper liquidity, but OKX occasionally offers better rates during market dislocations. Both exchanges use identical calculation methods, so rate differences primarily reflect liquidity depth and trader positioning."},{"question":"How do margin requirements compare for funding arbitrage?","answer":"OKX's portfolio margin allows cross-collateralization across positions, potentially reducing margin requirements by 20-40%. Binance uses isolated margin by default but offers cross-margin mode with less flexibility than OKX's unified account structure."},{"question":"Which platform is better for automated funding rate strategies?","answer":"OKX offers superior API infrastructure with WebSocket feeds for real-time funding rate updates and lower latency execution. Binance has broader market coverage but more restrictive API rate limits during peak periods."},{"question":"Do both exchanges offer the same altcoin perpetual pairs?","answer":"Binance lists approximately 200+ perpetual pairs compared to OKX's 180+ pairs. Binance typically adds new altcoin perpetuals faster, but OKX focuses on higher-quality projects with better liquidity sustainability for funding rate arbitrage."}]}]
